Description: BIOCLAIM™ is a comprehensive solution to healthcare fraud.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Miami Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: BioClaim™ is a patented software product that uses biometrics to authenticate a patient at the point of service. They place a biometric device (typically a fingerprint scanner) in a physician’s office to replace a conventional sign in sheet. BioClaim™ can also be used in conjunction with a smart card. When a patient enters the office, they will sign in using the biometric device by simply placing their finger on the scanner. They convert the biometric to a computer template. They never store the print so they are compliant with patient privacy. Also acquired during the visit is a patient identifier which is stored with the biometric id in their database. A registration code in the biometric device tells us which provider has which scanner. In every transaction they collect a patient identifier, a biometric print as well as a provider identifier (NPI or taxpayer ID), the date, time and location of the service. BioClaim™ has been under development since 2003. Development of BioClaim™ has always followed industry standards, giving users a choice of operating systems and hardware platforms. The market has since validated that foresight. Today, they still maintain hardware independence allowing their clients a wider choice of computer and operating system options including: all versions of Windows 32 bit operating systems and web browsers. They also allow a choice of networks that best meets your needs. BioClaim™ can be installed in a client-server network, a thin-client environment or be accessed via a web browser.

Description: Empowering consumers to get heard
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Nevahold is a service that seeks to eliminate the most frustrating and time consuming part in the customer service delivery process, by providing consumers with a unified platform that allows them to reach out to any company on the go. The service supports companies multiple contact channels to ensure the consumer’s voice is heard.  Nevahold receives a question or complaint from a consumer and posts it to the respective company’s customer support channels being Facebook, Twitter, email or any other support channel. The consumer goes about her daily activities and receives a response from the company through nevahold. If the brand does not respond to the consumer within a certain time frame nevahold blasts the company on all of its social media networks until there is a response.  Now instead of a consumer spending 30 minutes on hold for a customer support agent or searching online forums for an answer, she spends less than a minute to make her voice heard.
